</P>
<P>
   COLONIAL-LEGACY (Undated) In the closing years of this century,
historians, political scientists and other students of African
affairs have begun a searching re-examination of the continent's
recent past. Increasingly they have concluded that many of its most
persistent curses _ from the plague of ethnic hatred widely known
as tribalism to endemic official corruption _ have powerful roots
that are at least partly traceable to European subjugation and
rule. By Howard W. French. With map.
</P>
<P>
   ACADEMIC-JOBS (Undated) _ No one questions that Ph.D.s and
graduate students are in rough straits: Even the Modern Language
Association predicts that fewer than half of the 8,000 graduate
students finishing between 1996 and 2000 will land full-time,
tenure-track jobs within a year of getting their Ph.D.s. The fight
is over what constitutes a lifeboat: the corporate world or
organized labor? By Sarah Boxer.
</P>
