</P>
<P>
   CUBA-REVIEW (Miami) _ One year after Pope John Paul II visited
Cuba and urged the island nation to open itself up to freedom and
to the outside world, the Cuban government has made little progress
in improving its record on human rights, religious freedom and
economic reforms. By Larry Rohter.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUESTIONS OR RERUNS: (888) 346-9867 &LR;
