<P>
   w/CUBA-POPE _ HAVANA, Cuba _ It's been one year since Pope John
Paul II made his historic visit to Cuba. The visit brought a new
atmosphere of openness and reform to Cuba's one-party Marxist
society. But the church and the state are still in a tug-of-war
over just how much religious freedom should be allowed on the
island. While Cuba has released some political prisoners and has
granted visas for some foreign priests, the church remains closely
restricted by the state. We'll talk to church officials in Cuba and
in the United States to examine the events of the last year.
(Emling, Cox News Service). EDs: Photos to be placed in the
International folder on the Cox Server. EDs: Moving by noon Friday.
