<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Put your bets on Broncos
 &HT;    By Len Pasquarelli
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   Jets at Broncos, 4:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   _ TV: CBS (WGNX/Channel 46).
</P>
<P>
   _ Last week: Jets 34, Jaguars 24; Broncos 38, Dolphins 3.
</P>
<P>
   _ Series: Jets lead 13-12-1.
</P>
<P>
   _ Notable: This game features the AFC's two highest-rated
passers, the Jets' Vinny Testaverde (101.6) and the Broncos' John
Elway (93.0). ... The Jets' Bill Parcells is the first NFL coach to
lead three different teams to a conference championship game. ...
Jets running back Curtis Martin had 1,287 yards, the second-best
season in franchise history. ... Jets receiver Keyshawn Johnson
tied for the league high with seven TD catches on third down. ...
Denver has won 18 games in a row in Mile High Stadium and is 10-2
in home playoff games. ... Broncos running back Terrell Davis is
averaging 145.2 rushing yards per game in the postseason, the best
in league history. ... Broncos tight end Shannon Sharpe needs three
catches to pass Vance Johnson for the most playoff receptions in
club history.
</P>
<P>
   _ Favorite: Denver by 9.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
