A6156 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-AFC-MOORE17-COX     01-16 0615
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-AFC-MOORE17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    The continuing ``Dan and John'' soap opera
 &HT;    By Terence Moore
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ Just call it ``Dan and John.'' It is a soap opera that
sits only two victories away today from creating the most awkward
Super Bowl moments in 18 years. That's when NFL boss Pete Rozelle
nearly held his nose while handing the Vince Lombardi Trophy to foe
Al Davis.
</P>
<P>
   Now we're bracing for that soap opera, but only if coach Dan
Reeves' Falcons survive in Minnesota during the NFC Championship
Game and quarterback John Elway's Broncos ground the Jets for the
AFC title.
</P>
<P>
   Then, for the next two weeks along the way to that little game
in Miami, we'll have Dan and John, Dan and John, Dan and John. They
aren't bosom buddies, but there is something interesting here.
</P>
<P>
   Since these are supposedly the final days of Elway as the
Broncos' designated savior, his career is in full review throughout
the Rocky Mountains. Local TV stations have evolved into Elway
Central, and most of the highlights featuring Elway's 16 seasons
with the Broncos are from that opening decade of Dan and John.
</P>
<P>
   Reeves is prospering in his second season with the Falcons after
four years with the New York Giants. Before that, Reeves spent a
dozen years through 1992 leading the Broncos to four AFC
Championship Games, three Super Bowl trips and five AFC West
titles.
</P>
<P>
   Well, Elway likes to think that he was responsible for most of
the Broncos' goodness back then. Plus, since Reeves' firing by the
Broncos after the 1992 season, Elway has suggested that working for
Reeves was like shoving an upright down your throat.
</P>
<P>
   Elway sits behind Dan Marino in many of the NFL's all-time
records for quarterbacks. Still, to hear Elway tell it, Marino
would be chasing Elway in those categories if Elway hadn't spent
all of those seasons under the run-oriented Reeves.
</P>
<P>
   There also was Reeves' ousting of Mike Shanahan, the Broncos'
offensive coordinator and Elway's buddy, after the 1991 season.
Among other things, the coach said his trusted assistant for seven
years and his ungrateful quarterback forever were scripting plays
behind his back.
</P>
<P>
   Come to think of it, this soap opera could be ``Dan, John and
Mike,'' since Shanahan is in his fourth season as the Broncos' head
coach. While Reeves is a three-time loser in Super Bowls, Shanahan
won his first and only try at a world championship last season.
</P>
<P>
   Thus Elway's glee. Thus the possibility of this soap opera
making Rozelle and Davis resemble Laurel and Hardy.
</P>
<P>
   Leading up to Super Bowl XV, Davis battled Rozelle over the
right to move the Raiders from Oakland to Los Angeles. Then the
Raiders did the unthinkable by winning it all as a wild-card team
to force that face-to-face meeting between Rozelle and Davis on the
victory stand.
</P>
<P>
   That was tension. This could be worse. After the Broncos handled
the Falcons at the Georgia Dome last season, Reeves shook hands
with each of his former players but one.
</P>
<P>
   You've guessed it. So we held our breath this weekend after we
asked Elway if he'd talked with Reeves since his former coach
underwent quadruple heart surgery last month.
</P>
<P>
   ``No, I haven't,'' said Elway, quickly, before we asked him
about Reeves' success with the Falcons.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's done great,'' Elway said, smiling, before moving toward
his car in the distance. ``You have to give him credit for what
he's accomplished with them after just two years.''
</P>
<P>
   So maybe ``Dan and John'' wouldn't be a soap opera. Then again,
maybe it will never snow again in Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: tlmajc(at)aol.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
