<P>
   NFC CHAMPIONSHIP GAME PREVIEW COVERAGE
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFC-REEVES _ When Dan Reeves took the Falcons job two years
ago, he knew he would be coming back to his home state of Georgia.
But he didn't realize the true impact of ``home'' until he was
forced five weeks ago to undergo heart bypass surgery. Because of
the Falcons' success, Reeves had a good number of Georgians in his
corner. But his emotional press conference post-surgery galvanized
the entire state. Reeves said the experience changed his outlook
because he never could imagine how many Georgians genuinely cared.
As he uses all his postseason experience to prepare for the biggest
game in Falcons history, he's living an unusual love story.
(Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40-45. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   w/FBN-NFC-SOUND _ The Falcons spent much of the week practicing
in front of huge speakers that were shaking with the vibes of a
747. It's still no match for what the team can expect in the
Metrodome, the loudest venue in sports. The Braves dealt with it
once; the Falcons deal with it on Sunday. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFC-BIGGAME _ The players who have been in this position
have been schooling the young guys on the team about what to
expect. ONE GAME FROM THE SUPER BOWL. We eavesdrop on conversations
from Cornelius Bennett and Eugene Robinson. (Wilkinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFC-BESTSEAT _ The best seat in the house for a pro football
game is ... in your living room. TV coverage has become so
sophisticated that virtually nothing escapes the cameras on game
day. Whether its a shot between the legs of the center on a fumbled
snap, or a player kicking a water cooler on the sidelines, they
catch it all. A look at the technology that brings the game to you.
(Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH GRAPHIC (showing
Fox camera locations). MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFC-BIGKICK _ For 14 years, Falcons place-kicker Morten
Anderson has dreamed of making the game-winning kick and sending
the Saints or Falcons to the Super Bowl. For 13 years, he never
thought he'd get that chance. In high-caliber playoff games,
results often hinge on the final kick. Anderson is aware of that
... and he's ready. (Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
MOVED
</P>
