<P>
   IMPEACH _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton has so damaged the
presidency and broken faith with the public that the Senate must
convict him, House Republican prosecutors said Saturday as they
wrapped up their case in the nation's second presidential
impeachment trial. (Carr/Sherman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/IMPEACH-WITNESSES _ WASHINGTON _ Even before House prosecutors
had put the final flourishes on their three-day presentation
accusing President Clinton of high crimes and misdemeanors, several
prominent Senate Democrats were already asserting they had heard
nothing new. But while the Republican prosecutors may not have
changed many Democratic minds about the allegations against
Clinton, they appear to have made great strides toward achieving
their most crucial short-term goal: convincing enough Senate
Republicans that they must hear from live witnesses to reach a
verdict. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
