best he can to carry on his father's name and legacy of making
America freer of poverty, racism and violence. ``I never focused on
trying to be my father. I know I can't be that,'' King said
Saturday during in an interview at Tempe's first official Martin
Luther King Jr. holiday celebration. By BOB PETRIE. Story will move
